rn Iraq on Dec  7  2005  according to an obituary appearing in today s Virginian Pilot  Mr  Wright  32  was a civilian providing security services  He earned a degree in history  was a member of the football team for two seasons  and participated with the VMI Theatre  After graduation  Mr  Wright served in the U S  Marine Corps as an infantry officer and as a military intelligence officer  He left military service in 2000  He is survived by his parents  Gregory and Joan Wright  his brother  John Wright of Virginia Beach  his grandmothers  Marion Sullivan of Morrisonville  N Y  and Christine Wright of Randolph  N J  and numerous aunts  uncles  cousins  nieces and nephews  A viewing will be held at H D  Oliver Funeral Apartments located at 2002 Laskin Road  Virginia Beach  Va  from 3 to 5 p m  Sunday  Dec  11 and from 5 to 7 p m  Monday  Dec  12  A memorial service will be held at First Presbyterian Church located at 36th Street and Atlantic Avenue at 3 p m  Tuesday  Dec  13  An Irish wake will follow at the Cavalier Country Club  Information is available from the funeral home at  757  428 7880    UPDATE   12 DEC 05 A graveside service is scheduled at Quantico National Cemetery at noon  Wednesday  Dec  14 The cemetery is located midway between Washington  DC and Fredericksburg  Va  off Interstate 95 at South bound Exit 150B and North bound Exit 150 onto Route 619 West  Proceed three quarters of a mile on Route 619 West to the cemetery entrance on the left  Directional signs are posted on I 95 and Rt  619    VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master 